NAME
    jc - JSON Convert

SYNOPSIS
    jc [options] <parser> [input]

DESCRIPTION
    jc is a CLI tool and Python library that converts the output of popular command-line tools and file-types to JSON or YAML.

OPTIONS
    -a, --about         About jc
    -h, --help          Show this help message and exit
    -p, --pretty        Pretty print output
    -q, --quiet         Suppress warnings and errors
    -r, --raw           Raw output (no processing)
    -y, --yaml          YAML output
    -C, --color         Force color output
    -d, --debug         Debug output
    -m, --mono          Monochrome output
    -P, --parse-only    Parse the input only (do not process)
    -v, --version       Show version information and exit

USAGE
    Pipe the output of a command to jc with the appropriate parser, or use jc to parse a file.

EXAMPLES
    ls -l | jc --ls
    jc --ini /etc/my.cnf
    ps -ef | jc --ps
    cat /etc/passwd | jc --passwd

OUTPUT
    JSON or YAML representation of the parsed input.

BREAKDOWN
jc is a Python-based tool. When invoked, it uses the specified parser to interpret the input (either from a file or piped from another command), and then outputs the data in JSON or YAML format. The various options allow for customization of the output format and behavior.
